HEADWORD: Scrambled eggs
<hw>Scram"bled eggs</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Eggs of which the whites and
yolks are stirred together while cooking, or eggs beaten slightly, often
with a little milk, and stirred while cooking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

